# textures.config — which sprites the offline asset build precompiles, and how.
# Consumed by tools/textures/build_textures.py; outputs ship under wwwroot/Content
# and are loaded by WebContentManager in preference to the .png.
#
# Format (whitespace-separated, '#' = comment, blank lines ignored):
#   <asset-path>  <format>  [cols rows]
#
#   <asset-path>  Content-relative, lowercase, no extension. e.g. gfx/sprites/spider_sheet2
#   <format>      dxt | raw
#                   dxt  -> <name>.dds   BC3/DXT5, LOSSY, ~2.4x png on disk, tiny VRAM,
#                           zero decode. Needs texconv.exe. Sheet is auto-cropped to the
#                           largest multiple-of-4 that keeps the floor(W/cols) cell pitch
#                           (only never-sampled edge px are dropped) — Chrome/ANGLE rejects
#                           non-mult-of-4 block textures.
#                   raw  -> <name>.rtex  uncompressed straight-alpha RGBA8, LOSSLESS, large
#                           on disk, zero decode, any dimensions. For sheets where DXT
#                           artifacts show (gradients/soft glows).
#   [cols rows]   grid size for dxt sheets (the LoadAnimation columns/rows). Default 1 1.
#                 Ignored for raw.
#
# Assets NOT listed stay PNG: smallest download, but a slow StbImageSharp decode on the
# WASM main thread (the gameplay stutter the ?loadlog profiler hunts).
#
# Re-run after editing a source PNG or this file:
#   python tools/textures/build_textures.py
#
# NOTE (see Trello "Revisit per-sprite texture format"): the sprite art is being
# rescaled, so this list is intentionally minimal for now — two worked examples. Once
# the rescale lands, test each candidate IN GAME and pick dxt (default) or raw per the
# artifacts, then add it here.

gfx/sprites/spider_sheet2   dxt   7 7
gfx/sprites/large_asteroid  raw
